  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Plant 50,000 Native Trees for Refugees in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nearly 1,000,000 South Sudanese refugees have crossed into Northern Uganda where local farmers are already struggling to feed their families due to changing weather patterns. WildFF&apos;s project in Palorinya refugee settlement will combat this issue by planting native trees for food and firewood and providing high-efficiency cookstoves. This combined approach improves refugee life quality, combats climate change, and reduces pressure on local forests being rapidly deforested for resources.</narrative>
  </description>
